# File Organization

## One component per file

A `.tsx` file exports **one** public UI component (plus its `Props` type).

Extract a sub-component to its own file when it:
- has its own local state, or
- exceeds ~30 lines of JSX, or
- is referenced by more than one sibling.

```
src/app/auth/ui/settings/
  PasskeysCard.tsx      ✅ main card
  PasskeyRow.tsx        ✅ extracted row, not inlined
```

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — two components in one file
export const PasskeyRow = (...) => <li>…</li>;
export const PasskeysCard = (...) => <ul>…</ul>;

// ✅ GOOD — one file each
// PasskeyRow.tsx
export const PasskeyRow = (...) => <li>…</li>;
```

## Helpers out of component files

Pure functions, formatters, constants, and type guards must **not** live in a `.tsx` file. Move them to:

| Concern | Where |
|---|---|
| Domain logic / validation / hooks | `src/app/<feature>/domain/` |
| UI-local formatters / icon pickers | sibling `helpers.ts` in the same `ui/` folder |
| Server-only data fetchers | `src/framework/<area>/` (with `import 'server-only'`) |
| Cross-feature utilities | `src/lib/` |

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — helper in the component file
// ConsentsList.tsx
const titleCase = (slug: string) => slug.split('_').map(…).join(' ');
export const ConsentsList = () => { … };

// ✅ GOOD — helper in a sibling file
// helpers.ts
export const titleCase = (slug: string) => slug.split('_').map(…).join(' ');

// ConsentsList.tsx
import { titleCase } from './helpers';
```

## No comments in component files

Component files (`*.tsx`) must contain **zero** prose comments — no `//` or `/* */` lines.

- Explaining *what* a block does → the code itself should make it obvious; if it can't, refactor.
- Explaining *why* a non-obvious trade-off was made → put it in the `domain/` or helper file where the logic lives.
- TODOs → open a Linear issue instead.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — comments in a component file
export const ProfileForm = () => {
  // Reset form once the profile loads
  useEffect(() => { form.reset(…); }, [profile]);

  // Compute the minimal updateMask from dirtyFields
  const dirty = form.formState.dirtyFields;
  …
};

// ✅ GOOD — self-describing code, comments only in domain/
// domain/use_account_profile.ts (non-obvious session invariant — comment is fine here)
// Reset is gated on `profile` (a stable reference per SWR fetch) so
// the user's in-flight edits aren't clobbered on every revalidation.
```

This rule applies to `.tsx` files only. Comments **are** allowed in `.ts` files (domain logic, helpers, tests, server routes) where explaining invariants and trade-offs is valuable.

## Test files in `__tests__/`

Test files go in a `__tests__/` folder **sibling to the directory under test** — not colocated alongside the source file.

```
src/app/account/
  domain/
    initials.ts
    account_validation_schema.ts
  __tests__/
    initials.test.ts
    account_validation_schema.test.ts
```

```
// ❌ BAD
src/app/account/domain/initials.ts
src/app/account/domain/initials.test.ts   ← colocated

// ✅ GOOD
src/app/account/domain/initials.ts
src/app/account/__tests__/initials.test.ts
```

The vitest config already picks up `**/__tests__/**/*.test.ts` so no config change is needed.
